text: Yanceyville is a town in and the county seat of Caswell County, North Carolina, United States. As of the 2020 census, 1,937 people live in Yanceyvill and covered an area of 12.1 square kilometers, with a population density of 609.8 people per square kilometer. == References == Category:Towns in North Carolina Category:County seats in North Carolina
title: Yanceyville, North Carolina
